summary: This is a property deed and associated transfer documents for a two-family dwelling in Manhattan, recorded on April 28, 2016. The documents detail the sale of the property from one party to another, including tax forms, a smoke detector affidavit, and a water/sewer customer registration form.

events.title: Property Deed Execution
events.description: A deed was executed for the transfer of a two-family dwelling property in Manhattan from one party to another.

events.title: Deed Recorded with City Register
events.description: The property deed and associated documents were officially recorded and filed with the New York City Register's office.

locations: 59-17 Junction Boulevard, Flushing, NY 11373-5108 (NYC Department of Environmental Protection)
keyFacts: The document is a property deed for a two-family dwelling in Manhattan (Block 1, Lot 65), recorded on April 28, 2016.
The sale price of the property is listed as $3,750,000.00 on the Real Property Transfer Report (RP-5217).
Associated documents include a Smoke Detector Affidavit, a Water and Sewer Billing Customer Registration Form, and a Real Property Transfer Report, all required for the property transfer.

The grantor (seller) and grantee (buyer) parties are listed generically as 'party of the first part' and 'party of the second part' in the deed body; no specific individual or entity names are disclosed in the provided text excerpts.
The document shows significant transfer taxes were paid: NYC Real Property Transfer Tax of $214,818.75 and NYS Real Estate Transfer Tax of $211,050.00.
